    "report": "The attacker deposited 0.1 WBNB into the vault, then manually transferred 1000 BNB into the contract to deceive it into believing it had received 1000 BNB in rewards. This manipulation caused the contract to mint an excessive amount of MERL tokens as rewards. By exploiting this flaw in the reward calculation logic, the attacker was able to mint 8996 MERL tokens in a single transaction and ultimately extracted 332 BNB (approximately $100,000) per attack. The core issue was that the contract did not properly validate the actual source or legitimacy of the deposited funds when calculating the amount of MERL to mint.",
